com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util

Class PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util.PropagatorFunctionSource
      • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util.PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings

  • public class PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings
extends PropagatorFunctionSource
    A PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings implements a PropagatorFunctionSource by delegating all its functionality to an instance of a Bindings.

    A Bindings instance is associated to a specialization of a PropagatorFunctionBindings. It is provided by the latter thanks to the method PropagatorFunctionBindings.doGetBindings(), to be implemented by the concrete class.

    The Bindings allows to declare all the model elements the PropagatorFunctionBindings is depending on. This is typically static information, as it does not depends on the particular instance at hand.

    The Bindings implements all the functionality needed by the PropagatorFunctionSource: logic for touching, logic for collections the antecedents, managing the dependencies. It is not designed to be derived.
